  "text": "Time course assays were thereafter conducted in accordance with our previous description [CITATION_1] . Briefly, the standardized saline solution was used as seed culture for inoculum preparation. Seed culture (1% v/v) was inoculated into 150 mL of medium in 500 mL flasks (prepared in duplicates) and incubated on a rotatory shaker (160 rpm) at 28 °C . Samples were drawn every 24 h for a period of 10 days. Two milliliters of culture broth was centrifuged at 4000 g for 10 min and the cell free supernatant was used to determine the flocculating activity. The pH of the broth samples was also measured.",
